	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">peppers wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I use to have a nice program for playing swf files that also could convert them to an exe</div>
<br />If you open the swf in the <a href="http://www.adobe.com/support/flashplayer/downloads.html" class="postlink">Debugger Version</a> of the Flash Player you have the option of converting it to an EXE (goto File -&gt; Create Projector). Then you can use <a href="http://www.goldshell.com/versiown/main.htm" class="postlink">Versiown</a> to modify the icon, menus, etc to make it look more like a standalone application.
<br />
<br />EDIT: Except when the game hides the menu, which prevents you from selecting the "Create Projector" option. Well, I'm sure there is a workaround.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
